1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,244
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:44,608
Seriously? Math really said that?

3
00:00:44,692 --> 00:00:45,901
CHAPTER 50:
A CLASSIC, NOT A CLICHÉ

4
00:00:45,985 --> 00:00:47,069
I'm telling you he did.

5
00:00:47,862 --> 00:00:48,696
[chuckles]

6
00:00:48,779 --> 00:00:51,657
-So, how about this one?
-Uh, no.

7
00:00:52,491 --> 00:00:53,492
This one?

8
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:56,829
[sighs deeply]

9
00:00:56,912 --> 00:00:59,540
The problem is we don't know
what kind of style he prefers.

10
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:01,375
Feminine or sexy?

11
00:01:03,085 --> 00:01:05,337
I think he likes both feminine and sexy.

12
00:01:06,046 --> 00:01:07,590
He seems quite greedy, you know?

13
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:09,633
[gasps] Oh, hold on a sec.

14
00:01:10,134 --> 00:01:12,428
VIDEO CHATTING
EUI-JU, GO-YA

15
00:01:12,511 --> 00:01:13,679
Huh?

16
00:01:13,762 --> 00:01:15,431
[whimsical music playing]

17
00:01:15,514 --> 00:01:16,515
Ta-da.

18
00:01:18,058 --> 00:01:19,226
Seriously?

19
00:01:20,060 --> 00:01:21,061
You don't think

20
00:01:21,687 --> 00:01:22,855
it's a good choice?

21
00:01:23,355 --> 00:01:26,233
For a first date, it doesn't work?
[clicks tongue]

22
00:01:26,317 --> 00:01:27,318
[Woo-su] Eui-ju.

23
00:01:28,068 --> 00:01:29,069
Yes?

24
00:01:29,862 --> 00:01:30,946
What's your plan Saturday?

25
00:01:31,030 --> 00:01:32,031
[sighs]

26
00:01:32,740 --> 00:01:35,159
What on Earth could he want to talk about…

27
00:01:35,242 --> 00:01:38,078
[gasps] …just the two of us this weekend?

28
00:01:38,787 --> 00:01:40,414
[chuckles]

29
00:01:40,497 --> 00:01:41,957
Ah, I don't know.

30
00:01:42,499 --> 00:01:43,918
[breathes deeply]

31
00:01:44,001 --> 00:01:46,045
So what should I wear? [groans]

32
00:01:49,340 --> 00:01:52,176
[groans] Why is it only Thursday?

33
00:01:55,554 --> 00:01:58,474
[groans] Why is it only Friday?

34
00:02:00,976 --> 00:02:02,937
It's almost Saturday already.

35
00:02:03,812 --> 00:02:06,815
But why is time passing so slowly?

36
00:02:12,696 --> 00:02:13,781
[groans, sniffles]

37
00:02:17,785 --> 00:02:18,744
[exclaims]

38
00:02:19,328 --> 00:02:20,579
[bell rings]

39
00:02:21,455 --> 00:02:22,581
[server] Welcome.

40
00:02:22,665 --> 00:02:23,666
EPISODE 16

41
00:02:23,749 --> 00:02:26,418
-Did you have a reservation?
-Uh, yes. Probably. Yes.

42
00:02:26,502 --> 00:02:27,628
May I have the name for it?

43
00:02:27,711 --> 00:02:28,754
It's Ga Woo-su.

44
00:02:31,465 --> 00:02:32,758
Uh… I don't have it.

45
00:02:34,802 --> 00:02:35,928
Yeo Eui-ju?

46
00:02:36,011 --> 00:02:37,012
Yeo Eui-ju…

47
00:02:38,973 --> 00:02:40,057
Not that either.

48
00:02:41,475 --> 00:02:42,643
Anyway, there'll be two of us.

49
00:02:42,726 --> 00:02:45,020
-[chuckles] Sure. Please come this way.
-Yes. Thank you.

50
00:02:51,902 --> 00:02:53,904
[server]
Ma'am, let me get some water for you.

51
00:02:53,988 --> 00:02:54,989
Thank you.

52
00:02:56,699 --> 00:02:58,826
All right.
Please let me know if you need anything.

53
00:02:58,909 --> 00:02:59,910
Okay.

54
00:03:05,457 --> 00:03:07,668
What do I do? I'm so nervous.

55
00:03:08,252 --> 00:03:11,130
[Go-ya] Don't show it though.
He won't find you attractive.

56
00:03:11,797 --> 00:03:14,216
Order cream pasta. You know why, right?

57
00:03:14,299 --> 00:03:16,093
[Eui-ju] That's too much of a cliché.

58
00:03:16,635 --> 00:03:19,263
[Go-ya] Mm-mmm.
It's a classic, not a cliché.

59
00:03:19,346 --> 00:03:20,472
Trust me on this.

60
00:03:20,556 --> 00:03:23,308
[gentle romantic music playing]

61
00:03:31,442 --> 00:03:32,818
[server] Welcome.

62
00:03:39,283 --> 00:03:42,786
[tense music playing]

63
00:03:44,038 --> 00:03:45,039
[Eui-ju sighs]

64
00:03:55,007 --> 00:03:58,135
I guess Mr. Ga invited us to help us
patch things up.

65
00:03:59,386 --> 00:04:00,387
I guess so.

66
00:04:05,851 --> 00:04:07,311
-[door opens]
-[bell rings]

67
00:04:07,394 --> 00:04:08,437
[server] Welcome.

68
00:04:09,021 --> 00:04:10,022
You guys are early.

69
00:04:10,105 --> 00:04:11,231
-Did you have a reservation?
-Yes…

70
00:04:11,315 --> 00:04:12,775
…under "after-school" for 12 people.

71
00:04:12,858 --> 00:04:16,779
Uh… We have one under "Actors' School",
not "after-school" though.

72
00:04:16,862 --> 00:04:18,572
It's "after-school". After.

73
00:04:19,156 --> 00:04:19,990
[server chuckles]

74
00:04:20,074 --> 00:04:21,950
-Oh, it's still for 12 people, right?
-Yes.

75
00:04:22,034 --> 00:04:24,119
All right. Please have a seat there.

76
00:04:24,203 --> 00:04:25,329
Why are you guys there?

77
00:04:27,539 --> 00:04:28,540
[sighs]

78
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:33,087
-[students chattering]
-Oh, my gosh. This place is so nice.

79
00:04:33,796 --> 00:04:35,047
[student 1] Looks so good.

80
00:04:37,716 --> 00:04:39,593
-Thank you.
-Ah, I can't wait.

81
00:04:39,676 --> 00:04:41,845
I appreciate your hard work.

82
00:04:41,929 --> 00:04:42,930
Why don't we have a toast?

83
00:04:43,013 --> 00:04:44,640
-[student 2] Sounds great.
-[student 3] Sure.

84
00:04:44,723 --> 00:04:45,724
Good job.

85
00:04:45,808 --> 00:04:46,975
-Thank you!
-Thank you!

86
00:04:47,059 --> 00:04:48,102
[student 4] Thank you!

87
00:04:48,185 --> 00:04:50,854
Hey, why are you guys
all dressed up today?

88
00:04:50,938 --> 00:04:52,773
I know, you guys look so pretty today.

89
00:04:52,856 --> 00:04:55,150
Be… Because it's Saturday. [chuckles]

90
00:04:56,485 --> 00:04:57,736
This is awesome.

91
00:05:01,949 --> 00:05:02,950
[sighs]

92
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:04,034
[phone vibrates]

93
00:05:04,118 --> 00:05:05,994
[student 5] Mr. Ga, this is to die for.

94
00:05:06,078 --> 00:05:08,705
[Go-ya] How's the date going?
Send me some pictures.

95
00:05:09,373 --> 00:05:12,084
-Mr. Ga, can I have some of that too?
-Sure, go ahead.

96
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:13,836
-[student 5] Huh? Me too.
-Yes. [chuckles]

97
00:05:13,919 --> 00:05:14,920
[student 4] I want some too.

98
00:05:15,003 --> 00:05:18,715
Okay, should we take a pic
for the memories?

99
00:05:18,799 --> 00:05:20,843
-[chuckles]
-Sounds good. Let's do it.

100
00:05:20,926 --> 00:05:22,761
We need a picture together.
For sure. For sure.

101
00:05:22,845 --> 00:05:24,096
[chuckles]

102
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:28,016
[with mouth full]
Wait, you're blocking me.

103
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:30,686
One, two, three.

104
00:05:30,769 --> 00:05:32,604
WITH MR. GA
AFTER-SCHOOL MATH FINISHED

105
00:05:32,688 --> 00:05:33,897
[students cheering]

106
00:05:39,361 --> 00:05:40,863
[alarm beeping]

107
00:05:44,032 --> 00:05:45,033
[grunts]

108
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,161
[beeping stops]

109
00:05:48,579 --> 00:05:49,663
[sighs]

110
00:05:51,331 --> 00:05:52,374
[yawns]

111
00:05:54,835 --> 00:05:56,128
[sighs]

112
00:05:57,713 --> 00:05:59,756
[somber music playing]

113
00:06:24,364 --> 00:06:25,365
[breathes shakily]

114
00:06:27,075 --> 00:06:28,076
Dong-ju.

115
00:06:30,454 --> 00:06:31,455
Dong-ju.

116
00:06:32,456 --> 00:06:33,457
[door opens]

117
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:34,541
[Dong-ju] What is it?

118
00:06:37,544 --> 00:06:38,545
I can't see.

119
00:06:39,046 --> 00:06:40,047
[Dong-ju] What?

120
00:06:42,174 --> 00:06:43,425
Take me to the hospital.

121
00:06:43,926 --> 00:06:45,385
Okay, hold on.

122
00:06:46,887 --> 00:06:48,847
Hey, Gi-jeon. Gi-jeon. Wake up.

123
00:06:48,931 --> 00:06:51,058
-[Gi-jeon] What? What is it?
-[Dong-ju] Woo-su has a problem.

124
00:06:58,190 --> 00:07:00,025
[machine beeping]

125
00:07:07,074 --> 00:07:08,408
I can't see.

126
00:07:15,707 --> 00:07:18,961
[doctor] So your right eye had
a total corneal transplant before?

127
00:07:20,045 --> 00:07:21,046
Yes.

128
00:07:21,129 --> 00:07:25,801
What we can do for you now is
a deep anterior lamellar keratoplasty.

129
00:07:26,343 --> 00:07:29,846
It replaces part of the cornea
except for the inner endothelial layer.

130
00:07:32,224 --> 00:07:33,350
[Dong-ju sighs]

131
00:07:34,601 --> 00:07:36,353
He had the surgery ten years ago.

132
00:07:36,853 --> 00:07:37,854
He was fine.

133
00:07:37,938 --> 00:07:39,815
-No side effects afterward.
-Exactly.

134
00:07:41,650 --> 00:07:43,277
We all thought he was okay.

135
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,486
So why…

136
00:07:44,569 --> 00:07:45,654
[sighs]

137
00:07:46,530 --> 00:07:47,781
[crying]

138
00:07:48,657 --> 00:07:49,658
Hey.

139
00:07:50,492 --> 00:07:51,493
Are you

140
00:07:52,911 --> 00:07:53,954
crying?

141
00:07:54,955 --> 00:07:56,957
I feel so bad for that bastard.

142
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:00,919
[sobs] I knew when he played the smart-ass
and read all those damn papers.

143
00:08:01,003 --> 00:08:02,754
I knew this would happen, but…

144
00:08:02,838 --> 00:08:05,257
He didn't listen
and became a teacher, damn it.

145
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:07,259
I've been worried sick every single day.

146
00:08:07,342 --> 00:08:09,928
In case he'd end up like this
and give up on his studies.

147
00:08:10,012 --> 00:08:10,929
[sobs]

148
00:08:11,013 --> 00:08:13,056
-He's gonna be all right.
-[sniffles]

149
00:08:13,765 --> 00:08:15,726
Hey, what happened to all that trash talk?

150
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,311
Hey, come on.

151
00:08:17,394 --> 00:08:19,730
You know how much he cares for Woo-su.

152
00:08:20,522 --> 00:08:21,857
TREATMENT ROOM 1

153
00:08:23,066 --> 00:08:24,943
[gasping]

154
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,657
-Please register at the reception.
-Oh, okay.

155
00:08:32,242 --> 00:08:33,243
Are you all right?

156
00:08:33,910 --> 00:08:34,911
Yeah.

157
00:08:35,579 --> 00:08:36,955
So, what's the problem?

158
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,540
[Da-ju gasps] Hey, you're just an idiot!

159
00:08:38,623 --> 00:08:40,375
You think you're so smart

160
00:08:40,459 --> 00:08:42,586
but can't even take care
of your goddamn eyes.

161
00:08:42,669 --> 00:08:44,504
Why can't you do that one simple thing

162
00:08:44,588 --> 00:08:46,298
when all you do
is scold people for nothing,

163
00:08:46,381 --> 00:08:47,841
you arrogant prick?

164
00:08:48,925 --> 00:08:50,927
-Calm down, okay? Calm down.
-[breathes shakily]

165
00:08:51,011 --> 00:08:52,179
I'm getting surgery.

166
00:08:54,097 --> 00:08:56,141
Will that make your eyes better?

167
00:08:56,725 --> 00:08:57,976
[somber music playing]

168
00:08:58,477 --> 00:09:00,020
[doctor] Well, honestly speaking,

169
00:09:00,103 --> 00:09:03,732
there's a 50% chance
that your vision will recover to

170
00:09:04,858 --> 00:09:06,109
its pre-surgery state.

171
00:09:08,111 --> 00:09:12,157
Your cornea is exceptionally thin,
and the situation is quite complicated.

172
00:09:13,492 --> 00:09:16,244
Just don't exert yourself
and get plenty of rest

173
00:09:16,328 --> 00:09:18,080
until the surgery, okay?

174
00:09:18,955 --> 00:09:20,165
I'm going to get admitted,

175
00:09:20,832 --> 00:09:23,502
and they'll see
if my condition is suitable for surgery.

176
00:09:23,585 --> 00:09:24,586
[sniffles]

177
00:09:24,669 --> 00:09:26,505
Don't make a fuss and go home.

178
00:09:26,588 --> 00:09:28,298
Let's get you admitted first.

179
00:09:37,391 --> 00:09:40,060
-[chattering]
-[door opens]

180
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,897
-Hi.
-[students] Hello.

181
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:45,732
-Hello.
-He's here.

182
00:09:45,816 --> 00:09:47,192
[Dong-ju] Hello, everyone.

183
00:09:47,275 --> 00:09:50,195
[sighs] Your homeroom teacher won't be
coming to school for the time being,

184
00:09:50,278 --> 00:09:52,197
due to his eye problem.

185
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,865
So I'm here on his behalf.

186
00:09:54,699 --> 00:09:56,743
I'll be taking attendance.

187
00:09:57,619 --> 00:09:59,079
Mr. Yoon, Mr. Yoon.

188
00:09:59,663 --> 00:10:00,872
How bad is his condition?

189
00:10:00,956 --> 00:10:02,374
What exactly is wrong with him?

190
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:04,292
Uh…

191
00:10:04,376 --> 00:10:08,130
[sighs] I remember you said overdoing
himself would put his other eye at risk.

192
00:10:08,213 --> 00:10:09,548
What did you mean by that?

193
00:10:09,631 --> 00:10:11,508
If he's away for the time being,

194
00:10:11,591 --> 00:10:12,926
is he hospitalized?

195
00:10:13,009 --> 00:10:14,761
How long will he stay at the hospital?

196
00:10:16,221 --> 00:10:18,682
Eui-ju, don't you have a class to go to?

197
00:10:18,765 --> 00:10:22,102
[breathes shakily]
Which hospital is he staying at, huh?

198
00:10:22,185 --> 00:10:25,397
Just tell me that.
You can tell me that much, can't you?

199
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,481
[sighs]

200
00:10:29,025 --> 00:10:30,694
[doctor] Your cornea is a bit thin,

201
00:10:30,777 --> 00:10:33,989
but there shouldn't be any major problems
in proceeding with the surgery.

202
00:10:34,072 --> 00:10:37,617
It will definitely help sharpen your focus
and improve you vision in general.

203
00:10:40,328 --> 00:10:43,039
[somber music playing]

204
00:10:46,501 --> 00:10:48,753
-[sighs]
-[chuckles] Come on.

205
00:10:49,838 --> 00:10:50,839
Are you scared?

206
00:10:50,922 --> 00:10:52,424
[scoffs] No, I'm not.

207
00:10:52,507 --> 00:10:55,552
-[Gi-jeon chuckles]
-You were really in pain before,

208
00:10:55,635 --> 00:10:57,220
but you look all right now.

209
00:10:57,304 --> 00:10:58,388
[inhales deeply]

210
00:10:58,472 --> 00:11:02,267
Can't you have them do something
to make your double eyelids thicker?

211
00:11:02,350 --> 00:11:04,060
[chuckles]

212
00:11:04,561 --> 00:11:06,897
You don't do
personality transplants here, do you?

213
00:11:07,647 --> 00:11:08,690
[sighs]

214
00:11:11,359 --> 00:11:12,777
[sighs]

215
00:11:12,861 --> 00:11:14,529
Come on, man. Don't be a wuss.

216
00:11:15,822 --> 00:11:16,823
Good luck.

217
00:11:17,449 --> 00:11:18,617
See you later, four eyes.

218
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:19,701
-[chuckles]
-Wait…

219
00:11:19,784 --> 00:11:20,994
You don't have glasses.

220
00:11:21,077 --> 00:11:22,204
So, "geek" will do.

221
00:11:22,287 --> 00:11:23,288
[chuckles]

222
00:11:23,997 --> 00:11:25,248
You're feeling okay, right?

223
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:28,084
Good luck, huh.

224
00:11:28,919 --> 00:11:30,086
It's time to go now.

225
00:11:30,754 --> 00:11:31,755
Okay.

226
00:11:31,838 --> 00:11:33,006
See you.

227
00:11:33,089 --> 00:11:34,633
Don't cry, okay?

228
00:11:36,301 --> 00:11:37,844
-[Da-ju exhales sharply]
-Goodness.

229
00:11:37,928 --> 00:11:38,929
Yeah.

230
00:11:42,265 --> 00:11:43,266
[exhales sharply]

231
00:11:49,981 --> 00:11:51,399
[dramatic music playing]

232
00:11:52,275 --> 00:11:53,944
-Huh? What? Eui-ju?
-Hey!

233
00:11:54,027 --> 00:11:55,153
Hey, Eui-ju.

234
00:11:55,237 --> 00:11:56,947
Hey, Eui-ju. Where are you going?

235
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:58,907
-[Go-ya] Where?
-[Dan-ji] Did you see her face?

236
00:11:58,990 --> 00:12:01,993
[Dong-ju] He asked me to keep it a secret
until his surgery is over.

237
00:12:02,077 --> 00:12:04,955
He probably didn't tell anyone
in case they worried.

238
00:12:05,038 --> 00:12:07,082
He's at Hana University Medical Center.

239
00:12:12,212 --> 00:12:13,213
[doctor sighs]

240
00:12:13,713 --> 00:12:18,260
Fortunately, the surgery
went smoother than we previously expected.

241
00:12:18,343 --> 00:12:20,387
Are you feeling uncomfortable in any way?

242
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:21,763
-No, I'm all right.
-[chuckles]

243
00:12:23,473 --> 00:12:25,809
May I ask when I'll be able
to start reading again?

244
00:12:26,393 --> 00:12:27,978
Uh, give it about a week.

245
00:12:28,061 --> 00:12:30,730
It'll still be uncomfortable,
but you should be able to read.

246
00:12:32,274 --> 00:12:36,486
Full visual comfort though,
that could take three or four weeks.

247
00:12:36,987 --> 00:12:38,196
I see. Thank you.

248
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:40,949
[chuckles]
You just need to focus on recovering.

249
00:12:41,032 --> 00:12:42,242
[chuckles]

250
00:12:43,952 --> 00:12:45,495
[door opens]

251
00:12:46,663 --> 00:12:47,872
[sighs]

252
00:12:48,456 --> 00:12:49,708
[rapid footsteps approach]

253
00:12:53,753 --> 00:12:55,463
[gasps]

254
00:12:59,134 --> 00:13:00,135
[breathes shakily]

255
00:13:03,305 --> 00:13:05,432
Eui-ju, two demerit points
for ditching school.

256
00:13:05,515 --> 00:13:07,309
[breathing heavily]

257
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:11,271
[breathes shakily]

258
00:13:13,273 --> 00:13:14,274
[whimpers]

259
00:13:15,692 --> 00:13:16,693
Mr. Ga.

260
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,653
Are you okay, though?

261
00:13:22,365 --> 00:13:24,868
[breathes shakily]
Just tell me if you're okay.

262
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:29,623
About your ridiculous
absolute-value question…

263
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:33,585
My answer is…

264
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,467
the promise from ten years ago.

265
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:45,388
[child crying]

266
00:13:45,472 --> 00:13:47,849
[poignant music playing]

267
00:13:51,227 --> 00:13:53,438
Hey, are you in a lot of pain?

268
00:13:56,483 --> 00:13:57,484
YEO EUI-JU

269
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:59,110
[young Eui-ju] It's my mom.

270
00:13:59,194 --> 00:14:03,490
She said she won't let me
watch Pichi Pichi Pichi

271
00:14:03,573 --> 00:14:06,326
if I get the questions wrong again.

272
00:14:06,409 --> 00:14:07,869
[crying continues]

273
00:14:07,952 --> 00:14:09,079
[crying stops]

274
00:14:09,162 --> 00:14:10,538
Open your hands like this.

275
00:14:11,956 --> 00:14:14,751
Twelve means
all ten of your fingers plus two more.

276
00:14:14,834 --> 00:14:17,337
One, two, three, four, five…

277
00:14:18,672 --> 00:14:20,298
-It's seven.
-That's right.

278
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:23,051
So now whenever you do subtraction,

279
00:14:23,134 --> 00:14:26,262
try doing it from the two-digit number,
not the one-digit number.

280
00:14:26,346 --> 00:14:31,101
Does that mean that the ten-digit friend
is lending a hand to its one-digit friend?

281
00:14:31,184 --> 00:14:32,560
That's really nice.

282
00:14:33,269 --> 00:14:35,188
[young Woo-su] Right.
Let's try another question.

283
00:14:35,271 --> 00:14:38,233
[young Eui-ju]
Look, maybe I'm a genius now.

284
00:14:38,316 --> 00:14:40,485
Math is super easy.

285
00:14:40,568 --> 00:14:41,569
[chuckles]

286
00:14:41,653 --> 00:14:45,990
Now I'll get 100 on my math work,
and I'll show you the next time we meet.

287
00:14:46,574 --> 00:14:47,701
I promise.

288
00:14:49,828 --> 00:14:51,037
[giggles]

289
00:14:51,121 --> 00:14:52,122
[chuckles]

290
00:14:52,872 --> 00:14:54,082
Hmm.

291
00:14:58,795 --> 00:15:01,297
We met again ten years after that day.

292
00:15:01,381 --> 00:15:02,465
Yeo Eui-ju?

293
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,427
-Yeo Eui-ju!
-Over here.

294
00:15:06,803 --> 00:15:08,179
Four points.

295
00:15:08,763 --> 00:15:09,889
[Woo-su] A four in math?

296
00:15:11,641 --> 00:15:14,227
[chuckles] You just hate math, huh?

297
00:15:14,811 --> 00:15:18,440
You can't imagine the struggle
watching you try to keep that promise.

298
00:15:20,525 --> 00:15:22,402
Wow… [gasps]

299
00:15:22,485 --> 00:15:25,530
Those destined to meet
always do after all.

300
00:15:26,281 --> 00:15:27,991
We're meant to be.

301
00:15:28,074 --> 00:15:29,200
What?

302
00:15:30,618 --> 00:15:31,619
Uh, nothing.

303
00:15:31,703 --> 00:15:33,913
[chuckles] It's nothing.

304
00:15:33,997 --> 00:15:35,749
I remember now.

305
00:15:35,832 --> 00:15:38,960
You're that boy.
The handsome guy who was good at math.

306
00:15:39,043 --> 00:15:41,296
Whoa. [chuckles]

307
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:42,464
You remembered?

308
00:15:42,964 --> 00:15:44,132
You have no excuse now.

309
00:15:44,215 --> 00:15:45,216
Hold on.

310
00:15:45,759 --> 00:15:47,385
[gasps] This means,

311
00:15:47,469 --> 00:15:50,722
I was eight when I met you
for the first time

312
00:15:51,765 --> 00:15:54,642
and that's earlier than
when Deul-i met you, is that right?

313
00:15:54,726 --> 00:15:56,019
What?

314
00:15:56,102 --> 00:15:58,104
[chuckles] Yes. I win.

315
00:15:58,188 --> 00:16:00,940
[scoffs] Are you serious?

316
00:16:01,649 --> 00:16:02,650
[chuckles]

317
00:16:02,734 --> 00:16:03,610
[scoffs]

318
00:16:03,693 --> 00:16:04,944
Anyway,

319
00:16:05,028 --> 00:16:06,946
is she not coming to visit?

320
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:08,531
She's got no reason to.

321
00:16:08,615 --> 00:16:10,992
But isn't she… Isn't she your girlfriend?

322
00:16:11,576 --> 00:16:13,453
Not at all. We're just friends.

323
00:16:13,536 --> 00:16:14,746
Oh, come on.

324
00:16:14,829 --> 00:16:17,373
You have a different look on your face
when you're with her.

325
00:16:17,457 --> 00:16:19,459
You smile a lot. A sweet smile, you know?

326
00:16:19,542 --> 00:16:20,877
Something like this.

327
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:23,630
Don't you smile when you're with a friend?

328
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:25,298
Is that it?

329
00:16:26,174 --> 00:16:27,175
[clears throat]

330
00:16:27,258 --> 00:16:28,760
Then maybe… [inhales sharply]

331
00:16:28,843 --> 00:16:30,553
I can get my hopes up a little.

332
00:16:31,137 --> 00:16:32,013
What?

333
00:16:33,973 --> 00:16:34,974
Nothing.

334
00:16:35,934 --> 00:16:37,227
I wish you a quick recovery.

335
00:16:37,811 --> 00:16:38,812
[chuckles]

336
00:16:39,312 --> 00:16:40,647
Go home. I'm tired.

337
00:16:41,314 --> 00:16:42,857
-[grunts]
-Yep.

338
00:16:44,317 --> 00:16:46,027
-[sighs]
-[Eui-ju] Goodbye.

339
00:16:46,110 --> 00:16:47,779
Eui-ju, help me with this
before you leave.

340
00:16:48,613 --> 00:16:49,864
Sure! [giggles]

341
00:16:50,740 --> 00:16:51,866
I'm home.

342
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:53,785
-Hey, Mom.
-[with mouth full] Welcome home.

343
00:16:53,868 --> 00:16:55,745
-Mom, Mom, Mom, Mom, Mom.
-Hmm. What is it?

344
00:16:55,829 --> 00:16:58,998
Remember, remember when you took me
to that hospital in Seoul,

345
00:16:59,082 --> 00:17:00,416
what's that hospital called?

346
00:17:01,292 --> 00:17:03,503
What?
What are you talking about right now?

347
00:17:03,586 --> 00:17:04,796
This is so random.

348
00:17:04,879 --> 00:17:07,090
You know,
you took me to that hospital in Seoul,

349
00:17:07,173 --> 00:17:08,550
back when I was in first grade.

350
00:17:08,633 --> 00:17:12,595
What? Why would you see a doctor
when your mom's a pharmacist?

351
00:17:12,679 --> 00:17:15,431
You've never been sick enough
to go to a hospital.

352
00:17:16,808 --> 00:17:18,476
That's not true. I have.

353
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,645
[indistinct voices on television]

354
00:17:21,646 --> 00:17:22,647
I haven't?

355
00:17:23,273 --> 00:17:24,274
You haven't.

356
00:17:27,569 --> 00:17:29,904
Dad, I haven't?

357
00:17:32,198 --> 00:17:33,199
Huh?

358
00:17:33,825 --> 00:17:34,826
What the…

359
00:17:35,869 --> 00:17:36,870
When was it then?

360
00:17:39,247 --> 00:17:40,498
W-w-was it someone else?

361
00:17:40,582 --> 00:17:42,709
[mysterious music playing]

362
00:17:43,918 --> 00:17:45,044
[interviewer] Mr. Ga,

363
00:17:45,128 --> 00:17:47,672
you were well known for
being a math prodigy

364
00:17:47,755 --> 00:17:49,048
when you were just a young boy.

365
00:17:49,132 --> 00:17:50,508
CHAPTER 51:
THE NONSENSE ABSOLUT VALUE

366
00:17:50,592 --> 00:17:52,969
Could you tell me
what inspired you to become a teacher?

367
00:17:55,889 --> 00:17:57,724
Just before my second Olympiad,

368
00:17:58,308 --> 00:17:59,809
I withdrew from the competition.

369
00:18:00,685 --> 00:18:02,979
The official reason
was deteriorating eyesight,

370
00:18:03,563 --> 00:18:06,232
but the real reason was something else.

371
00:18:06,316 --> 00:18:08,026
During training camp,
I met this one other guy.

372
00:18:08,109 --> 00:18:09,485
GA WOO-SU
MATH TEACHER, MURIM GIRLS' HIGH

373
00:18:09,569 --> 00:18:11,321
He was always late because he overslept.

374
00:18:11,404 --> 00:18:14,574
He'd get caught reading comics
during problem-solving sessions.

375
00:18:14,657 --> 00:18:17,952
And yet, he breezed through
every problem I couldn't solve.

376
00:18:18,036 --> 00:18:19,245
-[Eui-ju chuckles]
-Bang.

377
00:18:19,329 --> 00:18:21,122
[Woo-su]
It was the first time I felt humbled.

378
00:18:21,205 --> 00:18:22,749
[chuckles]

379
00:18:22,832 --> 00:18:26,336
I could tell he had outstanding intuition
and that he genuinely loved math.

380
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:29,255
I knew I'd keep meeting people like that
through life,

381
00:18:30,423 --> 00:18:32,550
and I just didn't have
the confidence to keep going.

382
00:18:32,634 --> 00:18:34,594
I thought, "what should I do now?"

383
00:18:35,470 --> 00:18:36,930
I got my eye surgery,

384
00:18:37,013 --> 00:18:38,973
after dropping out of the Olympiad,

385
00:18:39,557 --> 00:18:42,518
and, at the hospital, I met a little girl.

386
00:18:45,146 --> 00:18:46,981
In that child's bright eyes,

387
00:18:47,065 --> 00:18:49,067
and the way she jumped up and down
with excitement,

388
00:18:50,109 --> 00:18:53,112
I was reminded of the moment
I first fell in love with math.

389
00:18:54,072 --> 00:18:55,949
And for someone who
had only ever been a student,

390
00:18:56,699 --> 00:18:58,534
it was the very first time

391
00:18:59,285 --> 00:19:01,788
that I felt true joy
in teaching someone else.

392
00:19:01,871 --> 00:19:03,206
[sighs]

393
00:19:03,289 --> 00:19:04,290
[interviewer] I see.

394
00:19:04,374 --> 00:19:06,584
So, I'm guessing that student
followed in your footsteps,

395
00:19:06,668 --> 00:19:09,295
competed in the Olympiad,
and obviously are really good at math.

396
00:19:11,965 --> 00:19:12,966
Well…

397
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,843
life rarely goes the way you want it to.

398
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:21,724
-[chuckles]
-Has she lost it?

399
00:19:23,101 --> 00:19:24,268
Now one last thing,

400
00:19:24,978 --> 00:19:28,439
can you tell us
what does math mean to you, Mr. Ga?

401
00:19:30,608 --> 00:19:31,609
[inhales sharply]

402
00:19:31,693 --> 00:19:33,444
TEACHERS' OFFICE

403
00:19:33,528 --> 00:19:35,488
[poignant music playing]

404
00:19:35,571 --> 00:19:37,073
[Woo-su] Math is…

405
00:19:40,702 --> 00:19:42,662
-Hello, Mr. Ga.
-Hello.

406
00:19:43,329 --> 00:19:44,330
[Woo-su] Math is…

407
00:19:45,915 --> 00:19:46,916
a process

408
00:19:47,542 --> 00:19:50,336
of discovering my own limits
at every single moment.

409
00:19:54,882 --> 00:19:56,884
[student 6] Oh, yeah. I can't wait.

410
00:19:56,968 --> 00:19:58,636
[student 7]
I wonder when he's gonna come in.

411
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,888
-Oh, hello.
-Hello.

412
00:20:08,604 --> 00:20:10,273
[mouthing] I got 55 points.

413
00:20:11,691 --> 00:20:12,692
[sighs]

414
00:20:19,949 --> 00:20:22,368
Great job on making it through
another boring school year.

415
00:20:22,452 --> 00:20:24,912
Yes, that's right.
We went through so much!

416
00:20:24,996 --> 00:20:26,456
-Good job, everyone!
-Yeah, we did it!

417
00:20:26,539 --> 00:20:27,915
-Good job, girls!
-We went through so much…

418
00:20:27,999 --> 00:20:29,375
-[laughing]
-…but we did it!

419
00:20:31,794 --> 00:20:33,171
And now you're gonna be seniors.

420
00:20:33,254 --> 00:20:34,756
[students groan]

421
00:20:34,839 --> 00:20:37,258
If you just spend your vacation
having fun,

422
00:20:38,301 --> 00:20:39,552
you'll regret it in March.

423
00:20:40,261 --> 00:20:42,346
I'm not telling you
to focus only on studying.

424
00:20:42,430 --> 00:20:43,681
Evaluate yourself.

425
00:20:43,765 --> 00:20:45,641
Know what you like and dislike.

426
00:20:46,225 --> 00:20:48,978
Learn what you're capable of
and what you want to achieve.

427
00:20:55,693 --> 00:20:56,694
Keep moving forward.

428
00:21:01,657 --> 00:21:04,494
I want you to have faith in
whatever path you choose, and walk on it.

429
00:21:04,577 --> 00:21:06,579
No matter what anyone else says.

430
00:21:11,334 --> 00:21:12,460
Each one of you

431
00:21:13,461 --> 00:21:14,462
is…

432
00:21:16,798 --> 00:21:18,841
a star that shines differently.

433
00:21:19,509 --> 00:21:21,010
[groaning]

434
00:21:21,094 --> 00:21:22,386
Oh, Mr. Ga.

435
00:21:22,470 --> 00:21:23,971
[students clamoring]

436
00:21:24,055 --> 00:21:25,431
It's sweet.

437
00:21:28,059 --> 00:21:30,436
I can't take it. He's so sweet.

438
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:32,146
[student 8] That was so sweet.

439
00:21:35,691 --> 00:21:38,361
[student 9] Aw, Mr. Ga. I love him.

440
00:21:38,444 --> 00:21:39,487
Dismissed.

441
00:21:40,530 --> 00:21:43,825
-Aw, thank you.
-Thank you.

442
00:21:43,908 --> 00:21:46,035
[students chattering, giggling]

443
00:21:46,119 --> 00:21:47,120
[student 10] Bye, Mr. Ga!

444
00:21:47,203 --> 00:21:49,038
[cheering]

445
00:21:49,122 --> 00:21:50,998
["Sweet & Sour" playing]

446
00:21:51,082 --> 00:21:52,125
CHAPTER 52:
I'M GLAD WE MET

447
00:21:52,208 --> 00:21:54,502
-[Eui-ju] What do you think?
-[Dan-ji] I really like it.

448
00:21:54,585 --> 00:21:57,797
"You and I are the closest at heart.

449
00:21:58,589 --> 00:22:00,508
A star that's distant for a moment,

450
00:22:00,591 --> 00:22:02,844
but close for a long time."

451
00:22:03,886 --> 00:22:05,179
-What do you say?
-Oh. [chuckles]

452
00:22:05,263 --> 00:22:06,639
Eui-ju and Go-ya, huh?

453
00:22:07,306 --> 00:22:09,267
-This is pretty nice.
-Not bad at all, you know.

454
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:10,393
[Dan-ji] I give you that!

455
00:22:10,476 --> 00:22:11,936
-[laughs] Nice job.
-[Jenny] I love it.

456
00:22:12,019 --> 00:22:13,229
I really do.

457
00:22:13,312 --> 00:22:15,189
-[Yeong-jae] You're the best.
-We did do a good job.

458
00:22:15,273 --> 00:22:17,692
[Dan-ji] "Close for a long time."
This is totally us. Don't you think?

459
00:22:17,775 --> 00:22:19,360
-[Yeong-jae] It's so like us!
-[Dan-ji] Oh, Eui-ju.

460
00:22:20,695 --> 00:22:23,239
Oh. I'll visit you for sure, okay?

461
00:22:23,322 --> 00:22:24,323
It better be soon.

462
00:22:24,407 --> 00:22:25,825
Okay. I'll make it real soon.

463
00:22:27,785 --> 00:22:29,370
-[sighs] Jenny.
-[chuckles]

464
00:22:29,453 --> 00:22:31,122
Don't forget about us.

465
00:22:32,540 --> 00:22:34,959
And don't ever dare to leave
our group chat, okay?

466
00:22:35,543 --> 00:22:38,045
I'll annoy you with emoji bombs
all the time.

467
00:22:38,129 --> 00:22:39,297
Please do.

468
00:22:39,380 --> 00:22:41,007
[both chuckling]

469
00:22:41,924 --> 00:22:43,092
All right. Bye, Jenny.

470
00:22:43,176 --> 00:22:44,594
[groaning]

471
00:22:45,178 --> 00:22:48,014
Well, make sure you get
a boyfriend by the time you come back.

472
00:22:48,097 --> 00:22:50,099
[all laughing]

473
00:22:50,183 --> 00:22:51,184
I will.

474
00:22:51,267 --> 00:22:53,519
Anyway, what's taking Eui-ju so long, huh?

475
00:22:53,603 --> 00:22:55,021
There she comes.

476
00:22:55,646 --> 00:22:57,523
-Run, guys!
-[Dan-ji] Eui-ju, hurry!

477
00:22:57,607 --> 00:22:59,609
-[Yeong-jae] What took you so long?
-You're so late!

478
00:22:59,692 --> 00:23:00,943
Come on, Ji-a… [panting]

479
00:23:01,027 --> 00:23:03,946
Ji-a wanted to say goodbye to Jenny,
and I waited until she was done working.

480
00:23:04,030 --> 00:23:05,323
Hey, when did I say that?

481
00:23:05,406 --> 00:23:06,699
Yes, you did. [laughs]

482
00:23:06,782 --> 00:23:10,453
Ji-a. Ji-a. Mmm.

483
00:23:10,536 --> 00:23:12,371
I can't get used to her hyper personality.

484
00:23:12,455 --> 00:23:13,456
I get it though.

485
00:23:13,539 --> 00:23:15,499
You guys are like a cat and a dog.

486
00:23:15,583 --> 00:23:17,084
-Meow! Woof! Woof!
-[chuckling]

487
00:23:17,168 --> 00:23:18,461
So true.

488
00:23:18,544 --> 00:23:21,088
I'm sorry that
I didn't look after you better.

489
00:23:21,172 --> 00:23:22,590
Take care of yourself out there.

490
00:23:22,673 --> 00:23:23,883
And eat this on your way.

491
00:23:25,259 --> 00:23:27,887
[groaning] Oh, my deskmate.

492
00:23:27,970 --> 00:23:29,889
-[all laughing]
-[Eui-ju] Geez.

493
00:23:30,514 --> 00:23:32,141
-Oh, don't cry.
-Thank you.

494
00:23:32,225 --> 00:23:34,393
Jenny, this is for you too.

495
00:23:34,477 --> 00:23:36,604
Take care and don't ever forget us, okay?

496
00:23:37,188 --> 00:23:38,022
Mmm.

497
00:23:39,482 --> 00:23:40,691
Ta-da!

498
00:23:40,775 --> 00:23:42,276
A STAR FAR AWAY

499
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,527
[all] Whoa! [laughing]

500
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:46,656
-[laughing]
-[gasps]

501
00:23:46,739 --> 00:23:48,199
[Dan-ji] No, it should be mine.

502
00:23:48,282 --> 00:23:49,283
Eui-ju.

503
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:52,203
[groans] Aw…

504
00:23:52,286 --> 00:23:54,872
Aw, I'm going to miss you.

505
00:23:54,956 --> 00:23:56,207
-Mmm.
-Me too.

506
00:23:56,290 --> 00:23:57,208
Thank you.

507
00:24:00,127 --> 00:24:01,462
[kisses]

508
00:24:01,545 --> 00:24:02,546
[all laughing]

509
00:24:02,630 --> 00:24:04,548
-Bye!
-Bye, Jenny! We love you!

510
00:24:04,632 --> 00:24:05,967
[Jenny chuckling]

511
00:24:06,050 --> 00:24:08,511
Guys, I'm right here!

512
00:24:09,679 --> 00:24:11,430
[chuckles] I'm here.

513
00:24:12,390 --> 00:24:14,684
[chuckles] I love you, girls!

514
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,144
Be safe!

515
00:24:17,228 --> 00:24:18,980
-Bye, bye, bye, bye!
-Bye, Jenny!

516
00:24:23,192 --> 00:24:24,568
[chuckles] See you soon!

517
00:24:25,569 --> 00:24:27,238
Bye! Love you!

518
00:24:29,198 --> 00:24:30,366
[sighs]

519
00:24:31,701 --> 00:24:33,786
I'm really happy I got to meet you all.

520
00:24:34,954 --> 00:24:35,955
[gasps]

521
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:41,752
Thank you for making
every day full of fun and laughter.

522
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:45,548
Every memory I have here in Korea
is with you girls,

523
00:24:45,631 --> 00:24:46,757
and…

524
00:24:47,675 --> 00:24:50,136
and I loved every single moment.

525
00:24:51,053 --> 00:24:54,056
I might be leaving,
but our friendship is forever.

526
00:24:54,807 --> 00:24:56,350
We'll meet again.

527
00:24:57,351 --> 00:24:59,770
Thank you for welcoming me warmly

528
00:24:59,854 --> 00:25:02,940
and making good memories with me.

529
00:25:03,024 --> 00:25:04,317
See you again.

530
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,484
Let me take your picture.

531
00:25:05,568 --> 00:25:07,028
-Good idea.
-Do it, do it, do it.

532
00:25:07,111 --> 00:25:08,612
-Stand here.
-[Dan-ji] Beautiful Korea.

533
00:25:09,739 --> 00:25:10,865
[shutter clicks]

534
00:25:10,948 --> 00:25:12,867
-Tteokbokki. I like tteokbokki.
-Do you like tteokbokki?

535
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:15,161
-Yeah.
-You do? It's so good.

536
00:25:15,244 --> 00:25:17,204
If you like spicy food,
you should try jjampong.

537
00:25:17,288 --> 00:25:19,206
What do you say to fried chicken or pizza?

538
00:25:19,290 --> 00:25:20,583
[laughing]

539
00:25:20,666 --> 00:25:22,585
[Eui-ju]
I was able to finish writing the novel,

540
00:25:22,668 --> 00:25:26,005
thanks to the support of my readers,
who desperately wanted me to resume.

541
00:25:27,631 --> 00:25:31,802
Later, the novel was launched
and reached over a million downloads.

542
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:34,472
It's so exciting. [gasps]

543
00:25:34,555 --> 00:25:37,391
I became a top-tier writer at last.

544
00:25:37,475 --> 00:25:39,393
Oh, you want to know how it ended?

545
00:25:40,227 --> 00:25:43,397
WE WERE FRIENDS, FINAL EPISODE

546
00:25:52,073 --> 00:25:53,824
[inhales sharply, sighs]

547
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:55,951
Okay. Fine.

548
00:25:56,452 --> 00:25:58,871
Now that I know
your heart belongs to Kang Tae-ha,

549
00:25:58,954 --> 00:25:59,914
[scoffs]

550
00:25:59,997 --> 00:26:01,082
I'll stop right now.

551
00:26:01,165 --> 00:26:03,501
-Si-on.
-[sighs]

552
00:26:03,584 --> 00:26:05,336
I told myself I'd never regret this.

553
00:26:06,170 --> 00:26:07,171
Turns out I do.

554
00:26:09,673 --> 00:26:11,384
I always was mean to you, wasn't I?

555
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:13,719
Thanks for everything, Choi Yoon!

556
00:26:13,803 --> 00:26:16,097
Come on, don't act like
we'll never see each other again.

557
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:18,391
Today will be the last time.

558
00:26:19,183 --> 00:26:20,226
Is that necessary?

559
00:26:20,309 --> 00:26:22,853
Si-on, you were my world in high school.

560
00:26:24,897 --> 00:26:26,816
I don't want to lose you.

561
00:26:28,692 --> 00:26:29,777
[scoffs]

562
00:26:31,112 --> 00:26:32,696
I know I'm the winner,

563
00:26:33,823 --> 00:26:35,449
but, strangely,
I don't feel pleased at all.

564
00:26:36,033 --> 00:26:37,201
You think this is a game?

565
00:26:37,284 --> 00:26:39,537
What do you win, huh?
A medal or something?

566
00:26:41,455 --> 00:26:42,790
You bastard.

567
00:26:42,873 --> 00:26:43,833
[tense music playing]

568
00:26:43,916 --> 00:26:45,418
[both breathing heavily]

569
00:26:47,128 --> 00:26:48,295
Uh, don't do this.

570
00:26:49,046 --> 00:26:50,047
-Huh?
-[sighs]

571
00:26:53,134 --> 00:26:54,260
I'm leaving.

572
00:26:54,844 --> 00:26:56,637
[gasps] Hey, Si… No, wait.

573
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,305
[Jae-min] Well…

574
00:26:58,389 --> 00:26:59,849
You guys were all here.

575
00:27:01,517 --> 00:27:03,144
I looked everywhere for you.

576
00:27:03,227 --> 00:27:06,063
Sit down. Sit down. Sit. Come.

577
00:27:09,358 --> 00:27:11,777
What's going on? What's with this mood?

578
00:27:11,861 --> 00:27:13,654
Did someone die or something?

579
00:27:13,737 --> 00:27:15,823
[laughing]

580
00:27:16,449 --> 00:27:18,159
I'm not in the mood for jokes now.

581
00:27:18,826 --> 00:27:20,035
You got dumped?

582
00:27:20,119 --> 00:27:22,121
-[sighs] Uh…
-[sighs]

583
00:27:23,038 --> 00:27:24,790
So you're giving up?

584
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,376
No…

585
00:27:28,377 --> 00:27:30,754
I'm not giving up on Yoon!

586
00:27:30,838 --> 00:27:32,256
-Hey, Han Jae-min.
-What? What?

587
00:27:32,339 --> 00:27:33,799
What do you want?

588
00:27:33,883 --> 00:27:34,758
Damn.

589
00:27:34,842 --> 00:27:38,929
Yoon, are you okay with
cutting ties with Si-on?

590
00:27:39,430 --> 00:27:40,723
No, right?

591
00:27:40,806 --> 00:27:42,183
Tae-ha, you too, punk.

592
00:27:42,266 --> 00:27:45,936
Are you sure you can be happy
while Yoon is sad?

593
00:27:55,821 --> 00:27:57,031
Let's all live together!

594
00:27:58,991 --> 00:28:00,034
Huh?

595
00:28:00,618 --> 00:28:02,411
-Together?
-The four of us.

596
00:28:03,454 --> 00:28:05,080
What's the big deal?

597
00:28:05,581 --> 00:28:08,667
You never truly know someone
until you've lived with them.

598
00:28:08,751 --> 00:28:09,752
-[sighs]
-Only then…

599
00:28:11,378 --> 00:28:12,796
you get to know their true colors.

600
00:28:13,506 --> 00:28:14,798
Uh…

601
00:28:14,882 --> 00:28:17,510
-[Jae-min laughs]
-Still, it's unnecessary to live together.

602
00:28:17,593 --> 00:28:20,346
Getting cold feet?
Then chicken out while you can.

603
00:28:20,429 --> 00:28:21,722
Ha! There's no way.

604
00:28:21,805 --> 00:28:24,183
[scoffs] I'm more than ready for it.

605
00:28:24,266 --> 00:28:25,893
[scoffs]

606
00:28:25,976 --> 00:28:28,103
-Still, I don't think this is--
-[shushes]

607
00:28:29,772 --> 00:28:30,689
[shushes]

608
00:28:30,773 --> 00:28:32,107
Don't worry,

609
00:28:32,191 --> 00:28:34,693
my baby deer.

610
00:28:34,777 --> 00:28:36,111
-[chuckles]
-Huh?

611
00:28:36,737 --> 00:28:38,322
It'll be super fun.

612
00:28:39,949 --> 00:28:40,950
As if.

613
00:28:41,450 --> 00:28:43,118
It's going to be a living hell.

614
00:28:43,202 --> 00:28:44,203
[chuckles]

615
00:28:46,539 --> 00:28:47,665
Is this round two?

616
00:28:48,499 --> 00:28:49,500
Oh, please.

617
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:53,212
All right, let's go!

618
00:28:53,295 --> 00:28:55,631
Here we come. Home, sweet home!

619
00:28:55,714 --> 00:28:57,508
Whoo! Bang, bang!

620
00:28:57,591 --> 00:28:59,176
All right, let's go!

621
00:29:09,937 --> 00:29:14,567
MOST POPULAR WEB NOVEL OF 2026
WE WERE FRIENDS

622
00:29:15,568 --> 00:29:16,610
[Shin] Here you go. [groans]

623
00:29:16,694 --> 00:29:17,778
FINAL CHAPTER:
FIRST SNOW

624
00:29:18,362 --> 00:29:19,446
-Honey…
-[grunts]

625
00:29:19,530 --> 00:29:22,116
…do you remember this?

626
00:29:22,199 --> 00:29:23,867
Oh, man. Yeah.

627
00:29:23,951 --> 00:29:27,413
This is when I went to the ER
for food poisoning. [groans]

628
00:29:27,496 --> 00:29:28,497
The ER?

629
00:29:29,540 --> 00:29:30,541
[Shin] Huh?

630
00:29:30,624 --> 00:29:34,086
Remember that time you fed me
all those raw oysters to boost my stamina,

631
00:29:34,169 --> 00:29:35,921
and I… [groans]

632
00:29:36,005 --> 00:29:38,132
[Ma] Oh, you mean when we went to Seoul?

633
00:29:53,355 --> 00:29:54,398
What's going on?

634
00:29:56,275 --> 00:29:57,735
You're leaving tomorrow, right?

635
00:29:57,818 --> 00:29:59,111
Are you done packing up?

636
00:29:59,945 --> 00:30:02,114
Mmm. Are you saying goodbye?

637
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:06,702
[Eui-ju] I came to give you this.

638
00:30:13,709 --> 00:30:16,795
I-I hear medical fees are expensive

639
00:30:16,879 --> 00:30:19,340
and it's not easy
getting medicine in the States.

640
00:30:19,423 --> 00:30:20,758
What if you get sick there?

641
00:30:22,217 --> 00:30:24,762
[inhales sharply]
You absolutely cannot get sick.

642
00:30:24,845 --> 00:30:28,641
And make sure you don't get too close
with Deul-i while you're over there.

643
00:30:28,724 --> 00:30:32,519
But don't go getting close
with the American girls either.

644
00:30:33,020 --> 00:30:35,564
Just study
and come straight back, all right?

645
00:30:36,231 --> 00:30:39,234
Oh, and watch out
for pretty American girls…

646
00:30:39,318 --> 00:30:42,363
Oh, and cute guys too.

647
00:30:42,446 --> 00:30:44,365
I guess you never know, right?

648
00:30:44,448 --> 00:30:48,410
And if anyone talks to you,
do not smile at them ever.

649
00:30:48,494 --> 00:30:49,536
Got it?

650
00:30:50,454 --> 00:30:51,455
[chuckles]

651
00:30:52,331 --> 00:30:53,707
Thank you. [chuckles]

652
00:30:54,375 --> 00:30:55,626
[groans]

653
00:30:55,709 --> 00:30:58,128
Oh, you really shouldn't smile like that.

654
00:30:58,712 --> 00:31:00,589
[sighs] This is not good at all.

655
00:31:02,841 --> 00:31:05,219
You're going to study
and do your research in the States

656
00:31:05,302 --> 00:31:06,970
only during vacation, right?

657
00:31:07,596 --> 00:31:09,348
You have to come back, okay?

658
00:31:10,224 --> 00:31:11,558
You don't have to worry.

659
00:31:12,476 --> 00:31:13,936
And good luck with your writing.

660
00:31:14,728 --> 00:31:16,313
What's your next project?

661
00:31:17,481 --> 00:31:18,524
[chuckles]

662
00:31:19,191 --> 00:31:20,401
The title is…

663
00:31:26,365 --> 00:31:28,242
[whispering]

664
00:31:29,827 --> 00:31:31,704
["Why the Night" playing]

665
00:31:35,457 --> 00:31:37,167
-[sighs]
-[chuckles]

666
00:31:38,419 --> 00:31:39,712
Have a safe trip.

667
00:31:41,088 --> 00:31:43,924
Thanks. Stay safe okay.

668
00:32:41,982 --> 00:32:44,443
[exclaiming]

669
00:32:44,526 --> 00:32:46,737
Mr. Ga! Mr. Ga!

670
00:32:47,321 --> 00:32:48,906
Mr. Ga, come back out!

671
00:32:49,740 --> 00:32:51,366
Look, it's snowing!

672
00:32:51,450 --> 00:32:53,660
It's the first snow! [laughs]

673
00:32:53,744 --> 00:32:55,329
The first snow.

674
00:32:57,122 --> 00:32:58,540
[laughs] It's snowing!

675
00:32:59,374 --> 00:33:01,335
Mr. Ga, it's the first snow!

676
00:33:07,132 --> 00:33:08,467
[Woo-su] Is that exciting?

677
00:33:11,512 --> 00:33:12,721
[Eui-ju] Of course!

678
00:33:13,514 --> 00:33:15,390
My first snow!

679
00:33:16,058 --> 00:33:17,476
The first snow!

680
00:33:18,143 --> 00:33:19,895
[laughs] My first snow!

681
00:34:03,438 --> 00:34:05,357
[students clamoring]

682
00:34:09,319 --> 00:34:11,655
["Sweet & Sour" playing]

683
00:35:11,006 --> 00:35:13,091
[students]
♪ Everything is sweet and sour ♪

684
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:17,137
[in Korean] ♪ This might be the real me ♪

685
00:35:18,722 --> 00:35:20,933
[in English]
♪ Everything is sweet and sour ♪

686
00:35:21,516 --> 00:35:23,894
[in Korean] ♪ Fill it sweetly ♪

687
00:35:23,977 --> 00:35:25,729
[in English] ♪ Sweet and sour ♪

688
00:35:25,812 --> 00:35:28,065
[cheering]

689
00:35:28,148 --> 00:35:29,691
-[song stops]
-[chairs clatter]

690
00:35:33,612 --> 00:35:35,489
[cheering]

691
00:35:35,572 --> 00:35:36,615
[song resumes]

692
00:35:53,006 --> 00:35:56,885
[chanting]

693
00:35:56,969 --> 00:35:59,262
-Jenny!
-Jenny!

694
00:35:59,346 --> 00:36:01,431
[cheering continues]

695
00:36:08,647 --> 00:36:11,066
[all, in Korean]
♪ What's really on your mind ♪

696
00:36:11,149 --> 00:36:12,734
♪ If you feel uneasy ♪

697
00:36:12,818 --> 00:36:14,569
[in English] ♪ You know it's all right ♪

698
00:36:14,653 --> 00:36:17,155
[in Korean]
♪ When you look up to the sky ♪

699
00:36:17,239 --> 00:36:20,325
[in English] ♪ It's sweet and sour ♪

700
00:36:20,409 --> 00:36:22,911
♪ Everything is sweet and sour ♪

701
00:36:23,704 --> 00:36:26,415
[in Korean] ♪ This might be the real me ♪

702
00:36:27,874 --> 00:36:30,210
[in English]
♪ Everything is sweet and sour ♪

703
00:36:30,877 --> 00:36:32,754
[in Korean] ♪ Fill it sweetly ♪

704
00:36:32,838 --> 00:36:35,215
[in English] ♪ Sweet and sour ♪

705
00:36:42,889 --> 00:36:45,600
[cheering]

706
00:36:45,684 --> 00:36:46,935
-Bye!
-Bye!

707
00:36:54,484 --> 00:36:57,237
THE END

